pull.title: [Docs] Updating benchmarkmarking.md with an updated sample output
pull.body:
This PR is just a documentation update for someone (or myself) that looks into finishing up #7883 in the future.

Looked through #7883 and appears [ryanofsky's PR](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/8873) setup the benchmarks, but there are `FIXME` comments to pull in data from `test/` to get a larger data set (assuming reason why 7883 is still open).

events.body:
Could also mention that a help message can be printed by `-?`.

```
  -?
       Print this help message and exit

@MarcoFalke Added a help section for the `-?` option.  Small cleanup to match format of other md files in `doc/`.  [Direct link](https://github.com/jeffrade/bitcoin/blob/benchmark_output/doc/benchmarking.md) for visual.

events.message: Updating benchmarkmarking.md with an updated sample output and help options
